markets.title: Will quarterly **nominal U.S. GDP growth** be above 3% in 2022 Q1?
markets.rules_primary: If U.S. nominal GDP growth in 2022 Q1 is above 3%, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
The market will always close at 8:25 AM ET on April 28, 2022. The data is expected to be released at 8:30 AM ET on that date.

Please see the Rulebook's Instructions section on how to calculate the Underlying. In short, go to the Source Agency link, click on the Edit Graph button and change "Units" to "Percent Change". The value in 2021:Q4 was 3.41%. Unlike for real GDP, the percent change itself is not annualized.
